Dataset ¶

The dataset and its detail description can be found under the following URL: https://www.kaggle.com/rpaguirre/tesla-stock-price
Dataset description is described from the owner as below

  • The Tesla stock price details are from the initial public offering from 06/29/2010 to 03/17/2017 (1692 data rows), also originally taken from the yahoo financing
  • Attributes:
    o Date - the date
    o Open the stock's opening price
    o High for That day's high price
    o Low for That day's low price
    o Close for the closing price of the day
    o Volume as of the sum of stocks exchanged in the day (the number of shares passed from one onwner to another in the day).
    o Adj Close indicates the closing price of the stock that has been changed to include any distributions / corporate actions that occur before opening the next day.

Moreover, for model evaluation, we used 10 other stock datasets. These datasets are derived from the original file containing 140 stocks from 2010 to end of 2016 downloaded from Kaggle (URL: https://www.kaggle.com/dgawlik/nyse?select=prices.csv).
This is the list of 10 stocks used for model evaluation: AAP, AAL, AAPL, BAC, BAX, BA, CA, CAH, CAG, DAL

def fn_load_data(realtime=0, p_stockName='TSLA', p_year=2):
    if (realtime==1):
        # Read data online from remote source                
        enddate = datetime.now()
        startdate = datetime(enddate.year - p_year, enddate.month, enddate.day)
        data_raw=DataReader(p_stockName, 'yahoo', startdate, enddate)
    else:
        data_raw = pd.read_csv('Tesla.csv', encoding= 'ISO-8859-1', index_col='Date', parse_dates=['Date'])
    # make a copy dataframe for working
    data=data_raw.copy()
    return data, data_raw

def sniff_modified(df):
    with pd.option_context("display.max_colwidth", 100):
        info = pd.DataFrame()
        info['data type'] = df.dtypes
        info['percent missing'] = df.isnull().sum()*100/len(df)
        info['nb of unique'] = df.apply(lambda x: len(x.unique()))
        info['unique values'] =  df.T.apply(lambda x: x.unique(), axis=1)
        return info.sort_values('data type')
    
def fn_check_missing_data_cols(data):
    df_info = sniff_modified(data)
    pd.set_option('display.max_rows', None)
    nb_missing_cols = len(df_info[df_info['percent missing']>0])
    if (nb_missing_cols ==0):
        print('There is no missing data cols in the dataset')
    return df_info, nb_missing_cols

def fn_scale_data(df):
    scaler = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=(0,1)) #desired range of transformed data between [0,1]
    df_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(df)    
    return df_scaled, scaler

def fn_split_data(p_X, p_Y, p_pct_train, p_pct_val):
    # p_pct_train is the percentage of train set. Example: p_pct_train=0.7
    # p_pct_val is the percentage of val set. Example: p_pct_val=0.1
    # test set is the remain
    
    nb_observation = p_X.shape[0]
    stop_point_train = int(np.floor(p_pct_train*nb_observation))
    stop_point_val = int(np.floor((p_pct_train+p_pct_val)*nb_observation))
    
    x_train=p_X[0:stop_point_train]
    y_train=p_Y[0:stop_point_train]
    
    x_val=p_X[stop_point_train:stop_point_val]
    y_val=p_Y[stop_point_train:stop_point_val]
    
    x_test=p_X[stop_point_val:]
    y_test=p_Y[stop_point_val:]
    
    return x_train, y_train, x_val, y_val, x_test, y_test


def fn_build_data_XY(df, p_look_back, p_predict_day):
    # For time-series problem, input variables for training usually include date series and features that are used for looking back and learning the trend of history
    print('1. Build X and y dataset that are input and target Variables')
    print('----------X dataset has sequences of date that is date series and all features')
    print('----------Y dataset has sequences of date that is date series and the feature "CLOSE"')
    print('----------The number of recent days to look back in order to predict the next day:', p_look_back)
    print('----------The number of predict day:', p_predict_day)
    X, Y = [], []
    nloop = (df.shape[0])-(p_look_back)-(p_predict_day)
    for i in range(nloop):
        X.append(np.array(df[i:i+p_look_back]))
        Y.append(np.array(df[i+p_look_back:i+p_look_back+ p_predict_day,-1:])) # (-1) is to get the last column that is column CLose (target column)
    return np.array(X), np.array(Y)

def fn_persistence(data):    
    print('================================================================================================================================')
    print('=                                                  PERSISTENCE                                                                 =')
    print('================================================================================================================================')
    
    n_pct_train,n_pct_val= fn_init()
    
    X=data['Open'].values
    Y=data['Close'].values

    x_train, y_train, x_val, y_val, x_test, y_test=fn_split_data(p_X=X, p_Y=Y, p_pct_train=n_pct_train, p_pct_val=n_pct_val)
    print('data.shape:',data.shape)
    print('x_train.shape:',x_train.shape, 'y_train.shape: ',y_train.shape)
    print('x_test.shape:',x_test.shape, 'y_test.shape: ',y_test.shape)
    print('x_val.shape:',x_val.shape, 'y_val.shape: ', y_val.shape)

    # define persistence model
    p_modelname='Persistence'
    def model_persistence(x):
        return x

    # validate
    y_pred = list()
    for x in x_val:
        y_pred.append(model_persistence(x))

    val_score = mean_squared_error(y_val, y_pred)
    print('Validation mean squared error of ',p_modelname,' model: %.3f' % val_score)

    # Test dataset
    y_pred = list()
    for x in x_test:
        y_pred.append(model_persistence(x))

    test_score = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)
    print('Test mean squared error of ',p_modelname,' model: %.3f' % test_score)
    

    plt.figure(figsize = (18,7))
    plt.title('Real data vs Predicted on the Test set Using Model '+p_modelname)
    plt.plot(y_test, 'tab:green', label='Real data')
    plt.plot(y_pred, 'tab:blue', label='Predicted')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
    return test_score

def fn_build_model_lstm(p_optimizer,p_activation, p_loss, p_input_shape):
    print('2. BUILD LSTM MODEL')
    print('----------Optimizer:', p_optimizer)
    print('----------Activation: ',p_activation)
    print('----------Input shape: ', p_input_shape)
    print('----------Loss: ',p_loss)  
    
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(LSTM(units=50, activation=p_activation, input_shape=p_input_shape))
    model.add(Dense(1))
    
    model.compile(optimizer=p_optimizer, loss = p_loss)
    return model


def fn_display_history(history):
    history.history.keys()
    history_dict = history.history # the dictionary that has the information on loss and accuracy per epoch
    
    loss_values = history_dict['loss']   # training loss
    val_loss_values = history_dict['val_loss'] # validation loss

    plt.plot(history.history['loss'], 'b', label="Training Loss")
    plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'], 'r', label="Validation Loss")
    plt.title("Training and Validation Loss")
    plt.xlabel("Epochs")
    plt.ylabel("Loss")
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
    return


def fn_train_model(p_modelname, model, x_train, y_train, x_val, y_val, x_test, y_test, p_epochs, p_batch_size, p_shuffle, p_verbose, scaler, p_silence=False, p_plot=True):
    if not(p_silence):
        print('3. MODEL TRAINING : ', p_modelname)
    
    start_time = time.time()    
    history=model.fit(x_train, y_train, epochs=p_epochs, validation_data=(x_val, y_val), verbose=p_verbose, batch_size=p_batch_size, shuffle=p_shuffle)
    
    if not(p_silence):
        print('----------Total Training Time (second):', time.time() - start_time)
        fn_display_history(history)   
    
    
    # Valiation dataset
    y_pred=model.predict(x_val)

    # invert scaling
    y_pred_inv = y_pred / scaler.scale_[0]
    y_inv = y_val / scaler.scale_[0]

    y_pred_inv=np.concatenate(y_pred_inv).ravel()
    y_inv=np.concatenate(y_inv).ravel()
    
    val_score = mean_squared_error(y_inv, y_pred_inv)
    if not(p_silence):
        print('Validation mean squared error of ',p_modelname,' model: %.3f' % val_score)
    
    # Test dataset
    y_pred=model.predict(x_test)

    # invert scaling
    y_pred_inv = y_pred / scaler.scale_[0]
    y_inv = y_test / scaler.scale_[0]

    y_pred_inv=np.concatenate(y_pred_inv).ravel()
    y_inv=np.concatenate(y_inv).ravel()
    
    test_score = mean_squared_error(y_inv, y_pred_inv)
    if not(p_silence):
        print('Test mean squared error of ',p_modelname,' model: %.3f' % test_score)
    

    if p_plot:
        if not(p_silence):
            print('4. PREDICTION USING TEST SET WITH MODEL ', p_modelname)   
        plt.figure(figsize = (18,7))
        plt.title('Real data vs Predicted on the Test set Using Model '+p_modelname)
        plt.plot(y_inv, 'tab:green', label='Real data')
        plt.plot(y_pred_inv, 'tab:blue', label='Predicted')
        plt.legend()
        plt.show()
        
    return history, y_inv, y_pred_inv

    
    
def fn_lstm(data):
    print('================================================================================================================================')
    print('=                                                  LSTM MODEL                                                                  =')
    print('================================================================================================================================')
    
    n_pct_train,n_pct_val= fn_init()
    
    data_scaled, scaler = fn_scale_data(df=data)
    
    n_look_back=7
    n_predict_day=1   
    X, Y = fn_build_data_XY(df=data_scaled, p_look_back=n_look_back, p_predict_day=n_predict_day)
    
    x_train, y_train, x_val, y_val, x_test, y_test=fn_split_data(p_X=X, p_Y=Y, p_pct_train=n_pct_train, p_pct_val=n_pct_val)
    print('data.shape:',data.shape)
    print('x_train.shape:',x_train.shape, 'y_train.shape: ',y_train.shape)
    print('x_test.shape:',x_test.shape, 'y_test.shape: ',y_test.shape)
    print('x_val.shape:',x_val.shape, 'y_val.shape: ', y_val.shape)
    
    
    p_modelname='LSTM'
    p_activation = 'sigmoid'
    p_optimizer='adam'
    p_loss = 'mean_squared_error'
    p_input_shape = (x_train.shape[1], x_train.shape[2])
    model = fn_build_model_lstm(p_optimizer,p_activation, p_loss, p_input_shape)
    
    p_batch_size = 128
    p_shuffle = False
    p_epochs=300
    p_verbose=2
    history, y_inv, y_pred_inv=fn_train_model(p_modelname, model,  x_train, y_train, x_val, y_val, x_test, y_test, p_epochs, p_batch_size, p_shuffle, p_verbose ,scaler)
    
    test_score = mean_squared_error(y_inv, y_pred_inv)
    return test_score

test_score=fn_lstm(data)

result={'model':['LSTM'],'test_score':[test_score]}

def fn_build_model_mlp(p_optimizer,p_activation, p_loss, p_silence=False):  
    if not(p_silence):
        print('2. BUILD MLP MODEL')
        print('----------Optimizer:', p_optimizer)
        print('----------Activation: ',p_activation)
        print('----------Loss: ',p_loss)  
    
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Dense(100, activation=p_activation))
    model.add(Dense(1))
    
    model.compile(optimizer=p_optimizer, loss = p_loss)
    return model  
    
def fn_MLP(data, p_silence=False):
    if not(p_silence):
        print('================================================================================================================================')
        print('=                                                  MLP                                                                         =')
        print('================================================================================================================================')
    
    n_pct_train,n_pct_val= fn_init()
    
    data_scaled, scaler = fn_scale_data(df=data)
    
    
    X=data_scaled # if take all but last column, use X=data_scaled[:,-:1]
    Y=data_scaled[:,-1:] # last column which is 'Close'

    x_train, y_train, x_val, y_val, x_test, y_test=fn_split_data(p_X=X, p_Y=Y, p_pct_train=n_pct_train, p_pct_val=n_pct_val)
    if not(p_silence):
        print('data.shape:',data.shape)
        print('x_train.shape:',x_train.shape, 'y_train.shape: ',y_train.shape)
        print('x_test.shape:',x_test.shape, 'y_test.shape: ',y_test.shape)
        print('x_val.shape:',x_val.shape, 'y_val.shape: ', y_val.shape)


    p_modelname='MLP'
    p_activation = 'relu'
    p_optimizer='adam'
    p_loss = 'mean_squared_error'
    # p_input_shape = (x_train.shape[1],1) #(x_train.shape[1], x_train.shape[2])
    model = fn_build_model_mlp(p_optimizer,p_activation, p_loss)

    p_batch_size = 128
    p_shuffle = False
    p_epochs=300
    p_verbose=0
    history, y_inv, y_pred_inv = fn_train_model(p_modelname, model,  x_train, y_train, x_val, y_val, x_test, y_test, p_epochs, p_batch_size, p_shuffle, p_verbose ,scaler)
    test_score = mean_squared_error(y_inv, y_pred_inv)
    return test_score

test_score=fn_MLP(data)

# store to compare with other models
result={'model':['MLP'],'test_score':[test_score]}
df_score=df_score.append(pd.DataFrame(result),ignore_index=True)

train_data, test_data = data2[0:int(len(data2)*0.7)], data2[int(len(data2)*0.7):]
training_data = train_data['Close'].values
test_data = test_data['Close'].values
history = [x for x in training_data]
model_predictions = []
N_test_observations = len(test_data)
for time_point in range(N_test_observations):
    model = ARIMA(history, order=(3,2,0))
    model_fitted = model.fit(disp=0)
    output = model_fitted.forecast()
    ypred = output[0]
    model_predictions.append(ypred)
    true_test_value = test_data[time_point]
    history.append(true_test_value)
MSE_error = mean_squared_error(test_data, model_predictions)
print('Testing Mean Squared Error {}'.format(MSE_error))


test_set_range = data2[int(len(data2)*0.7):].index

def fn_process_stock(data):
    n_pct_train,n_pct_val= fn_init()
    
    data_scaled, scaler = fn_scale_data(df=data)
    
    
    X=data_scaled # if take all but last column, use X=data_scaled[:,-:1]
    Y=data_scaled[:,-1:] # last column which is 'Close'

    x_train, y_train, x_val, y_val, x_test, y_test=fn_split_data(p_X=X, p_Y=Y, p_pct_train=n_pct_train, p_pct_val=n_pct_val)

    p_modelname='MLP'
    p_activation = 'relu'
    p_optimizer='adam'
    p_loss = 'mean_squared_error'
    
    model = fn_build_model_mlp(p_optimizer,p_activation, p_loss,p_silence=True)

    p_batch_size = 128
    p_shuffle = False
    p_epochs=300
    p_verbose=0
    history, y_inv, y_pred_inv=fn_train_model(p_modelname, model,  x_train, y_train, x_val, y_val, x_test, y_test, p_epochs, p_batch_size, p_shuffle, p_verbose ,scaler, p_silence=True, p_plot=False)
    return history, y_inv, y_pred_inv

for idx, stock in enumerate(p_stocklist):

    start_time = time.time()
    
    data_stock=data_full[data_full['symbol']==stock]
    data_stock.drop(columns='symbol',inplace=True)
    
    
    h, yi, ypi=fn_process_stock(data_stock)

    result={'stock':[stock],'test_score':[test_score]}
    df_mse=df_mse.append(pd.DataFrame(result),ignore_index=True)
    
    
    result={'stock':[stock],'mean_loss':[h.history['val_loss']],'processing_time':[time.time()-start_time]}
    df_loss=df_loss.append(pd.DataFrame(result),ignore_index=True)
    
print("Done")
